Author: AfriCodeWizard <AfriCodeWizard@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sat Dec 13 11:07:58 2025 -0800

    fix: resolve cross-domain rendering inconsistency with viewport and font-size
    
    - Add explicit viewport metadata export to layout.tsx
      - Ensures consistent viewport behavior across all domains
      - Prevents browser default viewport differences between vercel.app and custom domains
      - Sets initialScale: 1, maximumScale: 5, userScalable: true
    
    - Add explicit root font-size (16px) to html element in globals.css
      - Ensures consistent rem/em calculations across domains
      - Prevents iOS Safari text size auto-adjustment with text-size-adjust: 100%
    
    - Replace viewport-relative units (vw) with rem units in drip-text-section
      - Removes dependency on viewport width interpretation
      - Ensures consistent padding regardless of domain
    
    Root cause: Missing viewport metadata in Next.js App Router caused browsers
    to apply different default viewport settings on custom domain vs vercel.app,
    resulting in scaled-down appearance (smaller fonts, larger spacing).
    
    This fix guarantees pixel-consistent rendering across all domains and browsers.

